  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section firstReview">
      

<div id="review_2811574881" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2811574881" />
    <a title="Karina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34634845-karina"><img alt="Karina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1529438551p2/34634845.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2811574881?book_show_action=true">Jul 27, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Karina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Karina" href="/user/show/34634845-karina">Karina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2811574881" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16036533681951681343">Of all Habib&apos;s works, THE LEGENDARY WOLF is his best one yet. It&apos;s not just the story, but how the story is portrayed. The narrative style and prose is phenomenal. He has written many other emotional works, but the gravitas in THE LEGENDARY WOLF is something completely fresh for his writing. <br/><br/>This novel, as described by many other reviewers, is an action/thriller with a strong western flair. The story follows Grayson Wolf, a former government assassin. He was the greatest killer in the world deca</span>
  <span id="freeText16036533681951681343" style="display:none">Of all Habib's works, THE LEGENDARY WOLF is his best one yet. It's not just the story, but how the story is portrayed. The narrative style and prose is phenomenal. He has written many other emotional works, but the gravitas in THE LEGENDARY WOLF is something completely fresh for his writing. <br /><br />This novel, as described by many other reviewers, is an action/thriller with a strong western flair. The story follows Grayson Wolf, a former government assassin. He was the greatest killer in the world decades ago. But after going AWOL on his government before butchering the vice president and countless other officials one night, he has been living underground for nearly 25 or 30 years now. He spends every moment haunted by his demons and his past. When the story opens, Grayson has now grown old and is a shell of the man he once was. He is borderline suicidal, and he tries to take his own life every night. That all changes when an old comrade shows up on his front door. The comrade needs help protecting a young girl from the dark forces pursuing her, and Grayson is reluctantly pulled into all this. Unknown to him, this is his chance at redemption. <br /><br />Though it's a fast-paced and action-packed novel, the story stays true to its core and is a character-driven tale. There are a lot of themes/symbols utilized as the core of this novel. Wolves, especially grey wolves, are a major symbol of old warriors. It's a perfect symbol for Grayson. He once embodied everything a wolf brings to mind. But now he has become old. Three major themes I caught are: 1) the ramifications of violence 2) the theme of atonement 3) the theme of old age's loneliness. <br /><br />By telling the story in the 1st person POV, Habib really allows us to see the psyche of Grayson. He is cynical and holds a lot of self-hatred. This is what makes him suicidal. One of the great things Habib does is that he does not give us any more backstory about Grayson than we need. This allows Grayson to still be shrouded in a lot of mystery even though we find ourselves empathizing with him. His character arc is the treu essence of the story. There are tons of scenes where it is just him and his thoughts. Even when there are other characters, there is often minimal dialogue. Again, this makes us feel as if we are in his shoes many times. <br /><br />All these themes, symbols, and characters are interwoven in some TERRIFIC action and fight scenes. The scenes are not glamorous. Instead, they're dark, dirty, brutal, and often blood soaked. It's not violence just for the sake of it. No, it's all for a purpose and a greater theme. <br /><br />THE LEGENDARY WOLF is a story that I'll be reading again, and I definitely recommend it for readers of the genre and anyone who is looking for a phenomenal redemption story!</span>
  <a data-text-id="16036533681951681343" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


