<div id="review_2813000042" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2813000042" />
    <a title="William Adams" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/34634775-william-adams"><img alt="William Adams" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1528123827p2/34634775.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2813000042?book_show_action=true">May 07, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="William Adams" class="user" itemprop="url" name="William Adams" href="/user/show/34634775-william-adams">William Adams</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2813000042" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13202219719702080399"><b> Best Book I&apos;ve read this Year! </b><br/><br/>I received an advanced copy of this novel in exchange for an honest review. <br/><br/>This book has everything I love: a great tone, a protagonist whose mind you get the chance to see into, and a gritty story. Like the description mentions, this is a brutal tale of redemption. Grayson Wolf is a soldier who has lost his way, a soldier who has no more battles left to fight. He was once a legendary assassin, one who the whole world feared, but that was a long time ago. He&apos;s no</span>
  <span id="freeText13202219719702080399" style="display:none"><b> Best Book I've read this Year! </b><br /><br />I received an advanced copy of this novel in exchange for an honest review. <br /><br />This book has everything I love: a great tone, a protagonist whose mind you get the chance to see into, and a gritty story. Like the description mentions, this is a brutal tale of redemption. Grayson Wolf is a soldier who has lost his way, a soldier who has no more battles left to fight. He was once a legendary assassin, one who the whole world feared, but that was a long time ago. He's now waiting for the Grim Reaper to come and claim whatever is left of his soul, and he spends his days and night drowning himself in alcohol and haunted by his demons. Everything changes when an old comrade shows up needing his help. <br /><br />What I loved most about this work was that even with all the action, it never stops being a character-driven tale. We don't learn any more of Grayson's history than we need to, keeping that element of mystery there all while we follow him on this final "hurrah." The metaphors are strong with this one too, and Grayson's arc can be related to anyone who has lost their way or forgotten who they once were.<br /><br />All in all, I'd recommend this to anyone who is a fan of these kinds of works! </span>
  <a data-text-id="13202219719702080399" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
