        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2929339736" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3462318873394749152">5 STARS<br/><br/>Another great work by Habib, this novel is unlike any other he has written. But it has the same gravitas as his other works, like THE HEART OF ALEPPO and MEMORIES OF MY FUTURE. <br/><br/>Grayson Wolf is a perfect protagonist for this novel. A former assassin who has now become a shadow of the man he once was, he is a broken man now haunted by his demons as he waits to die. Everything changes when he suddenly finds himself forced to protect a young girl from dark forces pursuing her.<br/><br/>THE LEGENDARY WO</span>
  <span id="freeText3462318873394749152" style="display:none">5 STARS<br /><br />Another great work by Habib, this novel is unlike any other he has written. But it has the same gravitas as his other works, like THE HEART OF ALEPPO and MEMORIES OF MY FUTURE. <br /><br />Grayson Wolf is a perfect protagonist for this novel. A former assassin who has now become a shadow of the man he once was, he is a broken man now haunted by his demons as he waits to die. Everything changes when he suddenly finds himself forced to protect a young girl from dark forces pursuing her.<br /><br />THE LEGENDARY WOLF is a true-and-blue redemption story. There is a lot of symbolism/extended metaphors sprinkled in throughout the story, and that is what makes it so relatable to the reader. I found myself relating to Grayson more than I thought I would, and I soon found myself engrossed in his story. <br /><br />Even with all the brutal fight/action scenes, the novel never loses track of the fact that it is a character-driven tale. It is not about all the fights, chases, and journeys. It is about a man. It is about a broken man rediscovering his purpose. <br /><br />And that is why it is a great novel!</span>
  <a data-text-id="3462318873394749152" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

