              <span id="reviewTextContainer2811382303" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12848542026592098593"><b>Terrific.</b> <br/><br/>Like the description mentions, this is a powerful story of one man&apos;s redemption. The first-person POV is especially well-used in this novel, since it really helps the reader get into the head of Grayson Wolf. The tone is definitely gritty and not always pretty, and the action scenes certainly do not glamorize violence. The main theme is more about the cost of a violent life, and this theme is well-woven into the plot. <br/><br/>I found that even with Grayson&apos;s extraordinary circumstance, his cha</span>
  <span id="freeText12848542026592098593" style="display:none"><b>Terrific.</b> <br /><br />Like the description mentions, this is a powerful story of one man's redemption. The first-person POV is especially well-used in this novel, since it really helps the reader get into the head of Grayson Wolf. The tone is definitely gritty and not always pretty, and the action scenes certainly do not glamorize violence. The main theme is more about the cost of a violent life, and this theme is well-woven into the plot. <br /><br />I found that even with Grayson's extraordinary circumstance, his character arc is really a metaphor for what people experience as they grow older (loss of purpose, loss of friends, loneliness, etc.). In that way, I think readers will really be able to connect with this novel. <br /><br />Thank you to the author for the ARC!</span>
