<div id="review_2855855219" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2855855219" />
    <a title="Martha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/94907525-martha"><img alt="Martha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1552849950p2/94907525.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2855855219?book_show_action=true">Jun 12, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Martha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Martha" href="/user/show/94907525-martha">Martha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2855855219" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1567181030932560353">I&apos;m not really a huge fan of Westerns or novels with the western flair. Only rarely do I settle into this genre and find myself enjoying it. However, I was pleasantly surprised by THE LEGENDARY WOLF. <br/><br/>This book is a fast-paced, bloody chase. It&apos;s chalk full of morally questionable characters, with good and bad intentions. The setting is gritty and realistic. I will say that the writing style is rather... unadorned. But honestly it works well here and compliments the storytelling. It&apos;s a little st</span>
  <span id="freeText1567181030932560353" style="display:none">I'm not really a huge fan of Westerns or novels with the western flair. Only rarely do I settle into this genre and find myself enjoying it. However, I was pleasantly surprised by THE LEGENDARY WOLF. <br /><br />This book is a fast-paced, bloody chase. It's chalk full of morally questionable characters, with good and bad intentions. The setting is gritty and realistic. I will say that the writing style is rather... unadorned. But honestly it works well here and compliments the storytelling. It's a little strange to get used to if you're unfamiliar with this style of writing, but it wasn't much of a distraction.<br /><br />The story can come off as a little strong at times. I got the impression that is a textual criticism of the struggle people go through as they get old. Their family abandons them. They grow regretful. Their friends and companions die off or move away. And all these variables make them grow "stern" and "hard." That is the core of Grayson's struggle. His story is very fantastic, but the core is set in struggles that most people go through in their twilight years.<br /><br />I'll definitely be recommending this novel to friends! </span>
  <a data-text-id="1567181030932560353" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


