<span id="freeTextContainer1570475879165870383">Fast-paced, yet meaningful, this is a novel that fans of character-driven thrillers will certainly enjoy. Grayson Wolf was once the greatest assassin in the world and earned the nickname of Mors (the title of the Roman embodiment of death). Now an old man living a &quot;no-name&quot; life, he is a shadow of the legendary assassin he once was. However, the novel sees him getting a chance at redemption, a chance at burying the demons that haunt him every night. What follows is a thrill ride that leaves the </span>
  <span id="freeText1570475879165870383" style="display:none">Fast-paced, yet meaningful, this is a novel that fans of character-driven thrillers will certainly enjoy. Grayson Wolf was once the greatest assassin in the world and earned the nickname of Mors (the title of the Roman embodiment of death). Now an old man living a "no-name" life, he is a shadow of the legendary assassin he once was. However, the novel sees him getting a chance at redemption, a chance at burying the demons that haunt him every night. What follows is a thrill ride that leaves the readers on the edge of their seat. What I most loved about this is that even with all the brutal action, the harrowing fights, the novel never loses sight of the fact that it is a character-driven story about Grayson Wolf, the man behind all the legends. </span>
