<span id="freeTextContainer12289569917412569859">This is DEFINITELY far from my normal sort of read. The only reason I picked it up is because I&apos;ve enjoyed some of the author&apos;s other works. Nonetheless, this novel works on so many levels. Grayson Wolf start off as a broken man. One the greatest assassin in the world, he is now an old man who spends his days and nights haunted by the demons inside him. He gets a second chance at redemption, redemption in the form of protecting a young girl who is pursued by evil men, men that are similar and re</span>
  <span id="freeText12289569917412569859" style="display:none">This is DEFINITELY far from my normal sort of read. The only reason I picked it up is because I've enjoyed some of the author's other works. Nonetheless, this novel works on so many levels. Grayson Wolf start off as a broken man. One the greatest assassin in the world, he is now an old man who spends his days and nights haunted by the demons inside him. He gets a second chance at redemption, redemption in the form of protecting a young girl who is pursued by evil men, men that are similar and representative of Grayon's own past. This sort of plot can be seen as cliche, but Habib does it so well that readers will certainly enjoy following Grayson, following this legend, on his final hurrah! </span>
