<span id="freeTextContainer13097690014414018550">The story was fast paced, action packed, and fun. Grayson Wolf develops as a character over the course of the story, which is usually something that never happens in this genre. On the whole Ammar Habib had a fairly engaging writing style. All in all I enjoyed this and would read a sequel if one ever appears. It might even have reignited some enthusiasm in me for the thriller genre on the whole which is an unexpected plus. </span>

          </span>
