        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2856693266?book_show_action=true">Jun 13, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alexander R." class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alexander R." href="/user/show/98491434-alexander-r">Alexander R.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2856693266" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11520101648727603116">This is an examination of evil at its most primitive level, in which lawlessness, even in the modern world, reigns over conscience, reason &amp; morality. Grayson Wolf is the prototypical Boogeyman that is not immortal, though the concept of him will rule all the ages, prevailing like a force of nature. Powerful stuff, emotional &amp; heartless at the same time, &amp; of course, written in precise, minimalist prose. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


