      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781096820536" href="/book/show/51738469-the-legendary-wolf">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25185510-nay-denise?shelf=2019-favorite">2019-favorite</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2945228070" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4090662516633189409">Sooooo good!!! That ending killed me! I loved Wolf and little Anna. Such an action packed read!<br/><br/>Full review to come.<br/><br/>-------------------<br/><br/><b>Full review 8/26/19</b><br/><br/>This was such an excellent action packed novel! I loved it from start to finish. The depths, the emotions, the drama -- it gave me Jason Statham feels. The writing was well done. I always felt pulled into a scene be it emotional or fight scene.<br/><br/>Grayson Wolf is a man of mystery. He&apos;s dark and brooding. Emotionally weak, but physically strong. He d</span>
  <span id="freeText4090662516633189409" style="display:none">Sooooo good!!! That ending killed me! I loved Wolf and little Anna. Such an action packed read!<br /><br />Full review to come.<br /><br />-------------------<br /><br /><b>Full review 8/26/19</b><br /><br />This was such an excellent action packed novel! I loved it from start to finish. The depths, the emotions, the drama -- it gave me Jason Statham feels. The writing was well done. I always felt pulled into a scene be it emotional or fight scene.<br /><br />Grayson Wolf is a man of mystery. He's dark and brooding. Emotionally weak, but physically strong. He dealt with MAJOR hardships thanks to his job as an assassin. He was excellent at his job that he got the name Mors who was the Roman embodiment of death. He was a devil and a demon to many. After some horrible things take place he decides to use his skills to help the less fortunate.<br /><br />Grayson is such an amazing man. He was tormented by his past and always wanted to die, but he had such a huge heart. I loved how caring he was for others. He made me laugh, cry and scream. Learning about his past was heartbreaking. Seeing him turn into Mors was epic. Gray is such a phenomenal man and can definitely hold his own against hundreds. LOVED HIM!<br /><br />Jack -- oh my. I didn't expect his end so soon, but I loved him. Like Grayson, he was a big softie. He was caring and sweet. He sought to do good for people even though his skills were dark. I loved him.<br /><br />Anna was such a darling girl. She didn't deserve how she was treated. She was such an angel and true blessing to the world. Knowing the truth about her was insane! I mean seriously she was blessed, but it became her curse. I loved how responsible she was especially in her interactions with Gray. She had so much wisdom. Adored her!<br /><br />McCoy was a twisted man. He deserved to die the minute Jack found out the truth. He was a coward and greedy man. I didn't like him at all. Vasquez was ANNOYING from start to finish. I really couldn't stand him. Too cocky and wanted to be number one. That was his downfall.<br /><br />That ending <b>K I L L E D</b> me...why?!?!?!?!?!?! I loved it!<br /><br />Totally recommend this if you're looking for an action packed read!</span>
