<div id="review_2924973276" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2924973276" />
    <a title="Tallie T." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/100900098-tallie-t"><img alt="Tallie T." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1565010848p2/100900098.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2924973276?book_show_action=true">Aug 05, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tallie T." class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tallie T." href="/user/show/100900098-tallie-t">Tallie T.</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2924973276" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9568477127500532332">5 stars<br/><br/>Habib writes this novel with a level of gravitas that I saw in his other novel, THE HEART OF ALEPPO. The premise of the novel reminded me of other thrillers, like the Jason Bourne series. However, once the story starts to develop, it becomes something else entirely. There was a lot for a reader like me to love here. Grayson Wolf&apos;s internal conflict is so real and raw that it is easy to connect to what he is battling and his internal demons. The character arc he goes on is also believable </span>
  <span id="freeText9568477127500532332" style="display:none">5 stars<br /><br />Habib writes this novel with a level of gravitas that I saw in his other novel, THE HEART OF ALEPPO. The premise of the novel reminded me of other thrillers, like the Jason Bourne series. However, once the story starts to develop, it becomes something else entirely. There was a lot for a reader like me to love here. Grayson Wolf's internal conflict is so real and raw that it is easy to connect to what he is battling and his internal demons. The character arc he goes on is also believable since he does not change too quickly. As an older protagonist, one that has become disillusioned with the world, Grayson works well as the story's narrator and easily draws the reader in. <br /><br />That being said, the character development does not take away from the story line itself. The action scenes are brutal and violent, often ending in quite a bit of blood. The violence is as much of its own character as anything else, and it has a deeper meaning to the story and Grayson. <br /><br />This novel would make the perfect film if the chance ever arrises. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9568477127500532332" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


