        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2953444131" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14798968431960726931">Whoa. Alright, I knew The Legendary Wolf was likely to be a book I’d enjoy after reading the blurb. I wasn’t expecting to absolutely love this novel. It’s brutal, gritty, and action-packed. I was glued to this novel from beginning to end.<br/><br/>Grayson Wolf, a soldier who has lost his way, is a fantastically written protagonist. Seeing into his mind makes him such a well-rounded character and everything I love in a character-driven novel. His back story is rich, and his<br/><br/>Ammar Habib’s writing is fantasti</span>
  <span id="freeText14798968431960726931" style="display:none">Whoa. Alright, I knew The Legendary Wolf was likely to be a book I’d enjoy after reading the blurb. I wasn’t expecting to absolutely love this novel. It’s brutal, gritty, and action-packed. I was glued to this novel from beginning to end.<br /><br />Grayson Wolf, a soldier who has lost his way, is a fantastically written protagonist. Seeing into his mind makes him such a well-rounded character and everything I love in a character-driven novel. His back story is rich, and his<br /><br />Ammar Habib’s writing is fantastic. He’s found the sweet-spot between description and action that keeps a reader obsessing from beginning to end. Highly recommended!<br /><br />*I received a complimentary copy of this book as part of a blog tour with Prism Book Tours. All opinions are my own.*<br /><br />Find this review and more on my blog: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://jessicabelmont.wordpress.com/">https://jessicabelmont.wordpress.com/</a></span>
